CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 16, 1940, pg. 8 reads:" Camille Hood; Courier's correspondent in Cincinnati, came to the home office Friday to visit with the staff and get new ideas on her work in Queen City. She was house guest of the T.B. Hamiltons."
TitMainTitle: Camille Hood wearing fur stole, standing on steps to Pennsylvania Central airplane
